{
  "doc_id": "20388",
  "text": "More specifically, in native space our parietal lobe mean GM volume of left 59 / right 58 cm3 is nearly identical to the mean of the two other studies providing such volumes [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] (left 59 / right 57 cm3); however we had noticed~30% lower volumes in the older study [CITATION_3] previously [CITATION_4] . Correspondingly, for the different set of studies for which native total (i.e. GM+WM) parietal lobe volume are available [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] , our volumes of left 122 / right 119 cm3 are around a quarter higher (ratio~1.25) than the literature mean of left 96 / right 96 cm3. This may be due to protocol differences. For example, protocol illustrations indicate that the study with the smallest volume may have excluded the part of the parietal lobe posterior to the cingulate gyrus and anterior to the parieto-occipital fissure (supplementary material p. 99 in [CITATION_7] ).",
